## A. Executive Summary

Kiddies Academy needs a website that wins the trust of Indian parents in under 3 seconds, drives admission enquiries, and lays the groundwork for a future content-managed experience — all without rebuilding the frontend. This PRD defines every aspect of the Phase 1 static site and the Phase 2 admin-panel transition.

### Core Problem

Most nursery/primary school websites in India fall into two traps: either they look like 1990s clip-art fests, or they are generic SaaS website templates with no soul. Neither earns parent trust. Kiddies Academy must look like the premium option the moment a parent lands on it.

### The Solution

A hand-crafted, component-driven Astro JS static site that feels warm and child-friendly — but is built with the precision and performance of a modern SaaS product. Every section has a clear job: reduce doubt, build trust, and invite action.

### Business Impact

- Increase online admission enquiries by 60%+ over the current touchpoints.
- Build a digital brand that positions Kiddies Academy as the category leader in its city.
- Create a zero-maintenance-cost marketing engine via static hosting (Netlify/Vercel).
- Prepare the architecture so an admin panel can be added later without a full rewrite.

### Key Decisions Summary

| Decision | Choice | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Framework | Astro JS 5.x | Zero-JS by default, island architecture, SSG |
| Hosting | Netlify / Vercel | Free tier, CDN edge, instant deploys |
| Content Layer | JSON + Markdown | Admin-panel-ready, version-controllable |
| CSS Strategy | Tailwind CSS + custom tokens | Rapid development, consistent spacing |
| Images | WebP via Astro Image | Performance, lazy loading |
| Forms | Netlify Forms / Formspree | Static-friendly, zero backend |
| Analytics | Google Analytics 4 + Clarity | Free, Indian market standard |
| SEO | Custom SEO component | Automated meta, OG, schema |
| Phase 2 API | Directus / Sanity / Strapi | Headless CMS, API-first |

