## E. Design System Direction

### E1. Visual Philosophy

> *Child-friendly warmth meets premium school confidence. Think Montessori classroom meets Apple.com — clean, spacious, trustworthy, with pops of joy.*

The design must achieve three things simultaneously: make children feel excited, make parents feel safe, and make the school look professional.

### E2. Colour Palette

| Role | Hex | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| Primary (Deep Navy) | `#12304A` | CTA buttons, headings, nav, links |
| Secondary (Muted Teal-Blue) | `#2F6F8F` | Accents, highlights, dividers, badges |
| Accent (Soft Gold) | `#D6A65A` | Hover states, icons, tags, urgency |
| Background (Warm Cream) | `#F7F3EC` | Primary background, card backgrounds |
| Text | `#1E293B` | Body text |
| Soft Section Bg | `#EAF2F6` | Section backgrounds, card fills |

> Avoid: garish neon, black backgrounds, overly pastel washed-out combinations. Maintain contrast ratio 4.5:1+.

### E3. Typography

| Element | Spec |
|---|---|
| **Heading Font** | Nunito (Google Fonts) — rounded, friendly, readable, premium. |
| **Body Font** | Inter (Google Fonts) — highly legible, modern, professional. |
| **Accent / Tagline** | Nunito (bold, 700+) — for hero taglines. |
| **H1 Size** | 56–72px desktop │ 36–44px mobile |
| **H2 Size** | 40–48px desktop │ 28–32px mobile |
| **H3 Size** | 28–32px desktop │ 22–24px mobile |
| **Body Size** | 16–18px desktop │ 16px mobile |
| **Small / Caption** | 14px — minimum |
| **Line Height** | 1.6 for body │ 1.2 for headings |
| **Letter Spacing** | -0.01em headings │ 0 body |

### E4. Spacing & Layout Rules

- Base spacing unit: 8px. All spacing is multiples of 8.
- Section vertical padding: 80px desktop | 48px mobile.
- Container max-width: 1200px, centered.
- Card grid: 3 columns desktop | 2 columns tablet | 1 column mobile.
- Grid gap: 24px desktop | 16px mobile.
- Border radius: 12px cards | 8px buttons | 4px inputs | 24px pill badges.
- Box shadow: subtle (`0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)`) — no harsh drop shadows.
- Section backgrounds alternate: White > Light Blue Tint > White > Light Gray.

### E5. Hero Section Strategy

The hero must answer three questions in 3 seconds: Where is this? What is it? Why should I care?

- Full-viewport-height on desktop, 80vh on mobile.
- Layered composition: background photo (real school) + soft dark gradient overlay + text.
- Single bold H1, supporting subheadline, two CTA buttons.
- Trust strip below hero: "Affiliated by CBSE | Est. [Year] | [X]+ Happy Families | Rated [X]/5"
- Subtle entrance animation: text fades up, trust strip slides in.
- **Never** use auto-playing videos in hero — use poster image + play button.

### E6. Trust Signals (Critical for Indian Parent)

- CBSE/Board affiliation badge — prominently above the fold.
- Years established — "Nurturing children since 2010" builds confidence.
- Number of students/alumni — social proof.
- Teacher qualification strip — "All teachers are B.Ed. / NTT certified".
- Safety callout — "CCTV on every floor | Police-verified staff | GPS-tracked buses".
- Awards and recognitions — real ones only.
- Google rating widget or star rating display.
- Parent quotes — with photo and child's class for credibility.
- Principal's photo and name — puts a real face to the school.

### E7. CTA Placement Strategy

- **Primary CTA:** "Enquire for Admission" — in Hero, Nav (button), Admission section, and Page footer.
- **Secondary CTA:** "Download Brochure" (PDF) — About and Admissions pages.
- **Sticky CTA:** WhatsApp floating button — bottom-right, always visible.
- **Inline CTA:** Each programme card has "Learn More" and "Apply Now".
- **Micro-CTA:** FAQ has "Still have questions? WhatsApp us."
- **Rule:** Never have more than one primary CTA per section. Secondary CTA is always ghost/outline style.

### E8. Image Style Guidance

- Real photos only — no stock photos of children.
- Lighting: Warm, golden, natural. Avoid harsh flash.
- Composition: Children looking engaged, teachers smiling, facilities looking clean.
- Diversity: Include children of varied backgrounds.
- Format: WebP primary, JPEG fallback. Min 1200px wide for hero images.
- File size: <100KB for card thumbnails, <300KB for full-section images.
- Gallery: Consistent aspect ratios per section (4:3 for events, 1:1 for portraits).

### E9. Animation Guidance

- Philosophy: Animations should feel like a warm welcome, not a circus.
- Hero: Fade-in + translate-up (200ms ease-out) for text. No parallax.
- Cards: Subtle scale on hover (1.02 transform). 150ms ease.
- Section entrance: Intersection Observer fade-in as you scroll (stagger 100ms per card).
- CTA button: Gentle pulse on first load (once only, not looping).
- Reduced motion: Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — all animations disabled.
- Maximum: 300ms for transitions.

### E10. Do's and Don'ts

| Element | DO | DON'T |
|---|---|---|
| Colors | Use the defined palette consistently | Use garish neon or rainbow text |
| Photos | Use real school photos | Use stock photos of children |
| Fonts | Stick to Nunito + Inter | Mix 4+ fonts |
| CTAs | One primary CTA per section | Flood every section with 3 buttons |
| Text | Short, parent-focused copy | Academic jargon or 500-word blocks |
| Icons | Use consistent icon set (Lucide) | Mix multiple icon libraries |
| Cards | Consistent border radius and shadow | Different card styles per section |
| Mobile | Design mobile-first, then scale up | Design desktop, shrink to mobile |
| Whitespace | Generous padding and breathing room | Cram content to save space |
| Animation | Subtle, purposeful, fast | Looping, flashy, distracting |

